genresAdvancedInfo.name: macedonian metal
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Macedonian metal is a sub-genre of heavy metal that originated in Macedonia. It features fast, aggressive guitar riffs, complex drum patterns, and powerful vocals. Macedonian metal often incorporates elements of traditional Macedonian folk music, including the use of traditional instruments such as the gaida and kaval. The lyrics often focus on themes of national identity, history, and mythology.
